    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1732"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1732">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 419.11D29/57.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Price</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 18, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your May 16. Inform Foreign Office that decision of Panama judge, if affirmed by
                    Supreme Court, will constitute denial of justice, <pb facs="1108" n="992"
                        xml:id="pg_992"/> and that if Government of Panama stands upon such decision
                    in dealing with claims of this Government arising from Cocoa Grove affair, it
                    can not be regarded otherwise than as clear evidence that Government of Panama
                    does not desire to do justice in relation to American citizens. You will request
                    to be informed immediately when Supreme Court will render decision.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
